.IP \fImode\fP 1i
Specifies the mode of the operation.
.IP
If the value of this argument is 
.PN Replace , 
then the previous 
property value is discarded.
.IP
If the value is 
.PN Prepend 
or 
.PN Append ,
then the
type and format must match the existing property value.
For 
.PN Prepend , 
the data is inserted before the beginning of the 
existing data. 
For 
.PN Append , 
the data is appended to the existing data.
.IP
If the value is undefined, it is treated as defined with the correct type
and format with zero-length data.
